'''Cloud Mountain''' was the highest [[Mountain/Legends|mountain]] on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Cularin/Legends|Cularin]], located generally to the north of [[Gadrin and Hedrett]]. Its peak was always covered with clouds, which inspired its name.<ref name="TRW" />

The [[Tarasin]] used to say that the top of the mountain was not made of rock, but clouds. One day the mountain disproved that theory by [[Volcano/Legends|erupting]]. The resulting [[Groundquake/Legends|groundquakes]], [[Magma/Legends|lava]] and ashfall decimated the nearby Tarasin tribes. The surviving Tarasin banded together into the larger [[Hiironi irstat]], located a [[Kilometer/Legends|kilometer]] from the mountain.

The north face of the mountain had been clear-cut by [[Sunburst Mining]] when they attempted to [[Mining/Legends|mine]] the mountain. The [[Cloud Mountain mines|mines]] were soon abandoned, but an entrance remained three-quarters of the way up the mountain, and the jungle was slow to reclaim the barren mountain face.<ref name="TRW" />

Years later, the [[Cularin resistance]] used those same mines as a secret headquarters,<ref name="TRW" /> until it was discovered and attacked by their enemies of the [[Metatheran Cartel]].<ref name="ARv">{{LivingForce|Eye of the Sun: Revelation and Refutation}}</ref>

